Negative Testing Report
Project

Employee Salary Management HRMS

Purpose

The purpose of this negative testing audit is to identify how the HRMS behaves when users or clients send invalid, incomplete, unexpected, or unsafe data. In a payroll-related system, negative testing matters because incorrect inputs can silently corrupt salary records, create wrong employee data, or block payroll work.

This report focuses on form-level and API-level failure scenarios that are most likely to affect employee records, salary updates, authentication, and protected HRMS actions.

